Thank you! The TTL chip interface seems like a really good jumping off point, I'll give it a shot today. The original author didn't respond to PM, so I assumed he left his project behind though...<br /><br />The NES based tracker seems interesting, but I'm going to design a more real-time instrument. My final piece will eventually be an effects pedal, which will read the frequency of anything connected to it, be it guitar, piano, or even voice, and then parse it through a series of converters and my uC, then pass it to the 2A03 for NES conversion.<br /><br />Sorry if it sounds a little abstract, I've only worked out the first half of the circuit so far (frequency -&gt; uC), and I'm constantly changing how my uC analyzes the audio due to how it will eventually have to pass through to the 2A03.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4535">jarek</a> — Tue Aug 17, 2010 10:15 am</p><hr />
